						               													<description>To play K-Chess you need a box of 8 K-Drons (4 each of 2 colors) and a regular chessboard.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are only five (5) different types of pieces involved in this game:  pawns, knights, bishops, rooks and queens (no king).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of the game is to capture the opponent&amp;rsquo;s figures using all the chess rules of movement.  Each player has four (4) pawns at the start of the game located on the corresponding color square of the first row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At each turn the player can either move a piece or transform it into another on (up or down the scale) according to the following sequence (scale):  pawn-knight-bishop-rook.  Pawn can be transformed into queens by crossing the board to the opponents starting row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
